git clone https://github.com/your-username/simple-calculator.git
cd simple-calculator
# calculator.py

def add(x, y):
    return x + y

def subtract(x, y):
    return x - y

if __name__ == "__main__":
    num1 = float(input("Enter the first number: "))
    num2 = float(input("Enter the second number: "))

    print(f"Sum: {add(num1, num2)}")
    print(f"Difference: {subtract(num1, num2)}")
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit: add basic calculator script"
git push origin main
# Simple Calculator

A basic calculator that can add and subtract numbers.

## Usage

Run the `calculator.py` script and follow the on-screen instructions to enter two numbers. The script will then display the sum and difference.

